  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Hollow Verbs (الفعل الأجوف)",
      "titleArabic": "الفعل الأجوف",
      "content": [
        "Hollow verbs (الفعل الأجوف) have و or ي as their middle (second) radical. This weak letter undergoes changes in various conjugations.",
        "In the past tense, the middle radical appears as alif (ا). In the present tense, it appears as its original form (و or ي)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Middle radical is و or ي",
        "Past tense shows alif: قَالَ، زَارَ، نَامَ، صَامَ، كَانَ",
        "Present tense shows و or ي: يَقُولُ، يَزُورُ، يَنَامُ، يَصُومُ، يَكُونُ",
        "When sukūn appears, the middle letter may be dropped: قُلْتُ (I said)",
        "The vowel of the first letter indicates the original middle radical"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "قَالَ الْحَقَّ", "english": "He said the truth" },
        { "arabic": "زَارَ صَدِيقَهُ", "english": "He visited his friend" },
        { "arabic": "نَامَ الطِّفْلُ", "english": "The child slept" },
        { "arabic": "يَقُولُ الْحَقِيقَةَ", "english": "He says the truth" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Conjugation Patterns",
      "titleArabic": "تصريف الفعل الأجوف",
      "content": [
        "When conjugating with pronouns that require sukūn, the middle radical is removed and its vowel transfers to the first radical."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "قَالَ → قُلْتُ (the و transfers its dammah)",
        "زَارَ → زُرْتُ (visited)",
        "نَامَ → نِمْتُ (slept)",
        "صَامَ → صُمْتُ (fasted)",
        "كَانَ → كُنْتُ (was)"
      ]
    }
  ],
